
Function
--------
Function is a self contained block of statement. Every function performs some specific task.Functions are of two types : 
    
    a. Standard Function | Pre-defined function | Library function | Built-in function | In-built function : Functions whose definition part is already defined. Ex : pow(),sqrt(),abs() etc

    b. User-defined function : Functions whose definition part is designed according to programming needs. Ex : void show(){}, void display(){} etc. 

Advantages of function :  
1. Function reduces program size
2. Function reduces redundancy of code 
3. Function reduces complexity of code 
4. Debugging would be easier 
5. We can create n number of functions 
6. A function can be called n number of times 

Note : 
    function calling <---------> calling function 
    function definition <------> called function

Categories of function : 
a. No argument no return type 
   
      |------------------------->
   function                   called  
   calling                    function
      <-------------------------|

    addition();                 void addition()  
    (no argument)               {
                                     .....
                                     .....
                                }

b. No argument with return type 
    int | double res = addition();                int | double addition()  
    (no argument)                                 {
                                                     .....
                                                     return statement;
                                                  }

c. With argument no return type 
    addition(a,b);                void addition(int a,int b)  
    (with argument)               {
                                     .....
                                     .....
                                  }

d. With argument with return type 
    int | double res = addition(a,b);             int | double addition(int a,int b)  
    (no argument)                                 {
                                                     .....
                                                     return statement;
                                                  }

---------------------------------------------------------------------

class Demo{
    <access_modifier> <return_type>  <function_name> ()
    {
        .....
        .....
    }

    public | private | protected | default int addition(){
        ....
        ....
    }

    public static void main(String[] args){
        Demo obj = new Demo();
        obj.addition();
    }
}